wiki.content: 7 Things is the first single from Miley Cyrus's sophomore album, Breakout. It was released late May 2008 and was put on iTunes June 17, 2008. It was a major hit, peaking at #2 on iTunes Top 100 Songs and it has peaked at #9 on the Billboard Hot 100. The music video, released in June, features Miley and teenage girls dancing and singing about how they hate & love their boyfriends. It was Cyrus's second official music video, after Start All Over.
